    {
      "source": "target",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Passive voice can be a sneaky thing, but spotting it is relatively easy. You can identify passive voice by looking for sentences that have a subject performing an action, but the doer of the action is not explicitly stated. For example, \"The experiment was conducted by the research team\" is passive voice, whereas \"The research team conducted the experiment\" is active voice. To fix it, simply rephrase the sentence to make the doer of the action (the subject) the one performing the action, as in the revised example. This will make your writing more direct and engaging.",
